 stack that does not tie up cpu_resources with its 1 hour (3600,000)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="UN;lw6Jl#Q73T%F*vW%/"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=";fR(B$JVC]Ga9mE24AWi"><field name="TEXT">Also the 'if(false)' mini-stacks will be skipped by cpu, for further non-resource burdening</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="E[#c,vC(w`pR(=_#1I#_"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="9K)fi}VZ0BaX3q#X,l*/"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="U?JY+SysQB`PwmPLnS|W"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="_Z/IXylf)8%8~$3kX~P7"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Very Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="1U=t#+M0x-3(DUUx^jI="><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="2JAP}!d?Q@m3q;5KaFe~"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="s2}@lcW`Sl,,L]o7A10o"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="D%+F:#S?6H!Ao-q3vu#H"><field name="TEXT">Levels 1, 2, 2.1</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|M*}fRR1WgBkr-V*F;:q"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="p9$Im:)^@z_mJEE3U5e^"><field name="TEXT">* Level 1: Hardcoded Static via Actual_Numbers for MotorPower%</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="3+}hZ`]e_Yk),|pVYzdx"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="#nN;gn9+yh4~9VqcgA+N"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2: Softcoded Dynamic via Variables/Constants for MotorPower% </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="bBRRYj|W)$G@E69t=mJf"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Osbcpk5.FcEjOg**OyrG"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2.1 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="08P5xn::Z=h6haM+4wHs"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="@f}fB3`T=de5ha^#n,$M"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Xgh0~SIwe{SSHNuXdJVm"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="IaW(#1Kqiwm^2SwE%hF%"><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Bo!l4]_Un|L/7zIZIo)y"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ax:5p]dtgx15Hg`cf/dn"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="*]f,LN5dBR0Zh]`60[p,"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="bHGL!dz-^P8V~SqTJU{v"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="kM58g0fr?*kps3mx%LIM"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="FN9G|{S}C:n$Hdc]W5|x"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="34s!G7=aCZg0hLPXQ5]#"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="3?t-0{(+.4]%3MLsK)3)"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="d6;FWKnhIakmr8y-l4_q"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="dt40($/vEyvZ2,h%HQ_G"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="{X6dW_R/-dC_}|AlhXPO"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="$5VerF*%+Zrvc6Z_dq3V"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id=".Y/O?{)6sSs(EKi(@Wh#"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="KiTHD#7Vq7t+Ma;/@JH0"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="2S3UJm*MOS!cD6Wv}zI~"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ZgMtKOJA8ofz;Fb1#Xy]"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="2.FUT@}I.SG$9$bNz9`j"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="nSgClFkS0I35BK~,pCs;"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="H1-bI_;xrarAxwKE?}g_"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="0}be.^(Q6g{7)88Fn#s+"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="u`R!Y*c5eu.fuV-#u#X0"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="mhGYBfi:5*AGVrqnPHT4"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="h|Dgm|/Q)LxM?:SV.h+t"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="|QEWW~I9k^-u+v)^s[IK"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="in}60O?kXfI5djW=emyF"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="e65/:Ixw7Ga+}c1`%A$B"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="%x+HVih7_d~(bh0PNI|i"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="9PCMJ1nUU=o2~jOa*XMo"><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Roseb3nesAb=hB[Mx}h9"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="YR8cFtEOc390)e]tbQPl"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="mr|~KD@_#o(s:bz-U89Z"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="UXvphS^oB:ec,uiW88TB"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id=")Ad,(#Ixk~w^UEY_Ho6C"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="[tt8{|hVp^2M|kx(-k3["><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="[QUuZv,3{s`=y4^|]]n!"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="g|vdx4d)J2T+vo`i1b3V"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="9t[|jk*Db+G^|9?rvr.C"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="BXydP4RN/D4[3PCVzm(N"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="FusN+IVNNL8bUpOwr7/@"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="gDqfO%z{w?Jt79!tcZyn"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="an69Ts_Yo#}S75)jC!X~"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="7q-ST_xrH,C-|z#ks:E3"><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="U}-}g/1J|8F*xR@}}dc3"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="%yI/_Z^:=H~A#x#wgT)r"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="3%AQ]EyEu1cd2-Ee8q+{"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="qvihjH?MxvHW|Gl~6DY0"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="e^QZS(csIk;X?4ld(4o4"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="9xuk-)`D0F0OBDcxn_r8"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh